In deriving this result the infinite volume limit is very important. In a finite volume there is no spontaneous breaking of chiral symmetry, and therefore the quark condensate would vanish. The spectrum is discrete for finite V and the sum in eq. (2.29) does not develop an infrared singularity. If the chiral limit had been taken at finite V the chiral symmetry would have been restored. Obviously, the two limits m

0

! 0 and V ! 1 are not interchangeable.

