4.2 Relation to the Skyrme model

For the soliton description of baryons the chiral field is crucial. Let us therefore concentrate now on the chiral field while setting all the other meson fields to their vacuum value. Aside from the pseudoscalar mass term the effective meson action of the chiral field is then given by the quark loop Tr log(i@= \Gamma m(U )

fl

5

) where U = ,

y

L

,

R

is the chiral field, see eq. (3.16). In

leading order its derivative expansion is given by the nonlinear oe-model Lagrangian

L

