4.4 Chiral anomaly

In this section we will discuss how the chiral anomaly (see section 2.3) is represented in the effective meson theory (3.25). Defining the quantum theory via path integrals the anomalous symmetry breaking is realized by the non-invariance of the functional integral measure [49]; despite the fact that the classical action appearing as `weight' factor under the path integral is invariant under the considered transformation. The integral measure

DqD _q (4.57) is not invariant under chiral rotations

q(x) ! O/(x) = (U (x))

