DO/D _O/ = J (\Theta )DqD _q : (4.59) This implies that for the effective meson theory (3.25) the anomaly is contained in the fermion determinant A

F

. The proof of anomalous chiral symmetry breaking, reflected by the

relation J (\Theta ) 6= 1, is given in Appendix A for the simplified case of a Dirac operator containing besides the usual kinetic and mass term only a vector field

