! SU (2): (5.2)

Solitons are finite energy field solutions to the Euler-Lagrange equations. Finiteness of the energy requires the energy density to vanish for r = jrj ! 1. This implies that the soliton configuration U (x) asymptotically approaches a constant value (independent of the orientation

^ r) which, as a consequence of chiral symmetry, can be chosen to be unity:

U (x) ! 1I for r ! 1: (5.3) Hence all points at spatial infinity are identified thereby compactifying IR

