5.2 Emergence of the soliton

In general the effective meson theory results from integrating out the quark and gluon degrees of freedom contained in QCD. Then the baryons, which are originally built from N

C

quarks, emerge as solitons of meson degrees of freedom. In order to explain how the baryonic

character is encoded in the topological properties of the soliton we examine the spectrum of constituent quarks in the background of the chiral field. The corresponding Dirac Hamiltonian reads

h = ff \Delta p + fim(U )

