G = j + t (5.12) symmetry, i.e. [h; G] = 0. Hence the eigenfunctions of h carry good grand spin and parity. In order to examine the spectrum of (5.10) we parametrize the chiral angle by [66]

\Theta (r) = \Gamma nss

