Before presenting the numerical results one remark concerning the non-confining character of the NJL model has to be made. Obviously the transformation from Euclidean to Minkowski space is only well defined as long as the exponent in the Feynman parameter integrals (7.12) vanishes for large s along the path connecting these two spaces. In the absence of the soliton this is only the case for ! ! 2m. Beyond this threshold the regularization functions develop imaginary parts which measure the decay of the meson fluctuations into quark-antiquark pairs. Consequently the quantum correction to the soliton mass which stems from the zero modes is estimated by the truncated sum

