\Gamma 2

C

) and hence they are omitted. The numerical results for the baryon masses

are given in table 7.6. Reasonable agreement with the experimental data for the masses of the nucleon (939MeV) and the \Delta -resonance (1232MeV) are only obtained for constituent quark masses m ss 400MeV. Unfortunately S then is as low as 0.4 for the translational zero mode.

As a conclusive statement of this section we would like to mention that the mass of the nucleon is significantly lower than the soliton mass due to quantum corrections. In general

